											<span id="DataList1__ctl0_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I am now working on enhancing the security model for each page.&nbsp; The last time I worked on the security, it was to move it over to the existing `Roles` based security model.&nbsp; I programmed it this way as a beginning for what I want to implement now.&nbsp; </P>
<P>After the next patch, each page will have a global permission, which will either allow Everyone, Members Only, or Officers only to view.&nbsp; From there, certain pages will also have "micro permissions" that can be mananged as well.&nbsp; For example, you can set the Roster to let everyone view the Page, but only logged-in Members can see DKP information, and only Officers can see DKP totals.</P>
<P>Every page that has a configuration column will have a new field added to include logged in Members.</P>
<P>These features will be present in custom pages as well.&nbsp; You will be able to set permissions on the pages you make.&nbsp; This way if you have a strategy, or maybe a long-term plan you want only Guildmembers to see, you can lock it up.</P>
<P>I should have it done in a couple days..&nbsp;&nbsp; Post on the forums if you have an input or suggestions for this!</P></font></span>
