											<span id="DataList1__ctl5_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>As promised, I added support for the new (yet still broken) raid dump file in the Raid console.&nbsp; I also added a help page for the Raid Manager page so those who have never added a raid can learn how to do it.&nbsp; The new file is dumped to your eq directory when you click the Dump button in the Raid Console.&nbsp; It creates a new raiddump-YYYYMMDD-TTTTTT.txt file&nbsp; (Year/Month/Day-Time).&nbsp; Don`t change the file name, as I use the file name to parse the date/time of the raid (since it doesnt provide that info in the file itself... /bird SOE)</P>
<P>I left in support for the /who list cut/paste.. you just have to click the checkbox to enable it.. when the Dump thingy works in EQ though, use that.. its better and more reliable.</P>
<P>I also changed the cache to update immediatly after you enter a raid.. It was causing too much confusion with it adding later, people were thinking the raid wasn`t added at all.. which is understandable.&nbsp; So now when you add a raid, it will show up right away in your Raid List page. </P></font></span>
										</td>
	</tr><tr>
		<td>
											<TABLE style="HEIGHT: 21px" borderColor="#b0c4de" cellSpacing="0" borderColorDark="#b0c4de"
												cellPadding="0" width="100%" borderColorLight="#b0c4de" border="0">
