											<span id="DataList1__ctl8_Label1"><font face="Verdana" size="1"><P>I added a column on the Roster so players can put their total AA points.&nbsp; You can, of course, hide this column if you don`t want it by clicking the `Configure View` link on the roster (when you are logged in as an Administrator).&nbsp; You can edit this column by going into edit mode, and the player can edit it in their profile editor.</P>
<P>There was a bug in the roster edit that prevented you from editing it if you had columns hidden to everyone, including Admins.&nbsp; Prior to the fix you had to have the visibility to be set to atleast Admins to see it, so that you could edit.&nbsp; This has been fixed.</P>
<P>I looked around at methods that I might have forgotten to re-fill the cache after updates.&nbsp; This caused the roster, for example, to not show the correct number of raids or points when an admin would update it.&nbsp; I found a few, and fixed it.. there are probably more, I will find the rest and fix em.</P></font></span>
										</td>
	</tr><tr>
		<td>
											<TABLE style="HEIGHT: 21px" borderColor="#b0c4de" cellSpacing="0" borderColorDark="#b0c4de"
